<?xml version="1.0" ?><entry xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:planet="http://planet.intertwingly.net/"><id>https://blogs.princeton.edu/imabandit/?p=1340</id><link href="https://blogs.princeton.edu/imabandit/2018/10/07/remembering-michael/" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><title>Remembering Michael</title><summary type="xhtml"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>It has been a year since the tragic event of September 2017. We now know what happened, and it is a tremendously sad story of undiagnosed type 1 diabetes. This summer at MSR Michael was still very present in our … <a href="https://blogs.princeton.edu/imabandit/2018/10/07/remembering-michael/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">→</span></a></p></div></summary><content type="xhtml"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>It has been a year since <a class="liexternal" href="http://news.mit.edu/2017/celebrating-life-of-doctoral-student-and-alumnus-michael-b-cohen-1005">the tragic event of September 2017</a>. We now know what happened, and it is a tremendously sad story of <a class="liinternal" href="https://beyondtype1.org/former-facebook-engineer-dies-of-undiagnosed-type-1-diabetes/">undiagnosed type 1 diabetes</a>.</p>
<p>This summer at MSR Michael was still very present in our discussions, whether it was about some ideas that we discussed that last 2017 summer (acceleration, metrical task systems lower bounds, etc…), or just some random fun story.</p>
<p>I highly recommend to take look at the YouTube videos from the <a class="liinternal" href="https://simons.berkeley.edu/workshops/schedule/8815">November 2017 symposium</a> in memory of Michael. You can also take a look at his (still growing) list of <a class="liinternal" href="https://arxiv.org/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Cohen%2C+M+B">publications on arxiv</a>. In fact I know of an upcoming major paper so stay tuned (the premises are in <a class="liinternal" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JU9-DkECZCE">Yin Tat’s talk</a> at the symposium).</p>
<p>As always when remembering this tragic loss my thoughts go to Michael’s family.</p></div></content><updated planet:format="October 08, 2018 12:39 AM">2018-10-08T00:39:43Z</updated><published planet:format="October 08, 2018 12:39 AM">2018-10-08T00:39:43Z</published><category term="Uncategorized"/><author><name>Sebastien Bubeck</name></author><source><id>https://blogs.princeton.edu/imabandit</id><link href="https://blogs.princeton.edu/imabandit/feed/" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://blogs.princeton.edu/imabandit" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><subtitle>Random topics in optimization, probability, and statistics. By Sébastien Bubeck</subtitle><title>I’m a bandit</title><updated planet:format="February 27, 2020 11:57 PM">2020-02-27T23:57:05Z</updated><planet:http_status>200</planet:http_status><planet:module>toc</planet:module><planet:format>atom10</planet:format><planet:items_per_page>40</planet:items_per_page><planet:face>bubeck.jpeg</planet:face><planet:name>S&amp;eacute;bastien Bubeck</planet:name><planet:http_last_modified>Tue, 07 Jan 2020 17:39:56 GMT</planet:http_last_modified><planet:bozo>false</planet:bozo><planet:http_etag>&quot;3a0c4fcd91cab62e790532ed250dce7a&quot;</planet:http_etag><planet:css-id>s-eacute-bastien-bubeck</planet:css-id></source></entry>